HEADWORD: Pirouette
<hw>Pir`ou*ette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; of uncertain
origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A whirling or turning on the toes in
dancing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Man.)</fld> <def>The whirling about of a
horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pirouette</ent>⟦br⟧

